### Variables
@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000/api
@token = TU_TOKEN_AQUI

### =====================
### AUTH
### =====================

### Registrar usuario
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Juan Pérez",
  "email": "juan@ejemplo.com",
  "password": "MiPassword123",
  "age": 25
}

### Login
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "juan@ejemplo.com",
  "password": "MiPassword123"
}

### Obtener usuario actual
GET {{baseUrl}}/auth/me HTTP/1.1
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### =====================
### TRACKS
### =====================

### Listar tracks (público)
GET {{baseUrl}}/tracks HTTP/1.1

### Obtener track por ID
GET {{baseUrl}}/tracks/65f8b3a2c9d1e20012345678 HTTP/1.1

### Crear track (requiere auth)
POST {{baseUrl}}/tracks HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "title": "Mi Canción",
  "duration": 180,
  "genres": ["rock", "pop"]
}

### Actualizar track
PUT {{baseUrl}}/tracks/65f8b3a2c9d1e20012345678 HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "title": "Canción Actualizada",
  "duration": 200
}

### Eliminar track (solo admin)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/tracks/65f8b3a2c9d1e20012345678 HTTP/1.1
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### =====================
### TESTS DE ERROR
### =====================

### Sin token (401)
POST {{baseUrl}}/tracks HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Sin Auth"
}

### Token inválido (401)
GET {{baseUrl}}/auth/me HTTP/1.1
Authorization: Bearer token_invalido

### Validación fallida (400)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "email-invalido"
}

